{"id":"1804.07359","submitter":"Alain Moise Dikande Pr.","authors":"Remi J. Noumana Issokolo and Alain M. Dikande","title":"Nonlinear periodic wavetrains in thin liquid films falling on a\n  uniformly heated horizontal plate","comments":"21 pages, 6 figures, submitted to Physics of Fluids","journal-ref":"Physics of Fluids (AIP) vol. 30, 054102 (2018)","doi":"10.1063/1.5027370","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.flu-dyn nlin.PS","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A thin liquid film falling on a uniformly heated horizontal plate spreads\ninto fingering ripples that can display a complex dynamics ranging from\ncontinuous waves, nonlinear spatially localized periodic wave patterns (i.e.\nrivulet structures) to modulated nonlinear wavetrain structures. Some of these\nstructures have been observed experimentally, however conditions under which\nthey form are still not well understood. In this work we examine profiles of\nnonlinear wave patterns formed by a thin liquid film falling on a uniformly\nheated horizonal plate. In this purpose, the Benney model is considered\nassuming a uniform temperature distribution along the film propagation on the\nhorizontal surface. It is shown that for strong surface tension but relatively\nsmall Biot number, spatially localized periodic-wave structures can be\nanalytically obtained by solving the governing equation under appropriate\nconditions. In the regime of weak nonlinearity, a multiple-scale expansion\ncombined with the reductive perturbation method leads to a complex\nGinzburg-Landau equation, the solutions of which are modulated periodic pulse\ntrains which amplitude, width and period are expressed in terms of\ncharacteristic parameters of the model.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Apr 2018 20:06:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-29"}
